    {
      "id": "e691f530d2ac0eefb08deedc51a39edeb994b96b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-22 04:57:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nandreas, I think we can just change meaning of *_NBUF from \"buffer number for a service\" to \"buffer number to allocate when growing the pool\", although each partition has its own buffer pool, but number of partitions is not linear increasing with number of cores, so it will give a better control of total memory.",
